Notes: The 60’s classic player series is a run of guitars Fender produced featuring 60’s specs but with improvements to suit the needs of modern players, including a 9.5 inch radius, and a 2 point tremolo. The sonic blue finish on this guitar is similar to the Stratocasters both John Lennon and George Harrison bought together, one of which Harrison turned into “Rocky” which was used on the Sgt. Peppers album. This particular Stratocaster has a slim, comfortable neck that allows for easy bending. The pickups are low output making this strat relatively quiet but still has plenty of spank.
